The paper deals with the problem of blind deconvolution, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of semi-definite programming and spectral bounds, which are common techniques in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The paper also involves numerical analysis and stability analysis, which are relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Systems and Control).
